modules.description: This module defines core utilities for encoding values into JSON format. It includes functions for serializing basic types like strings, integers, and booleans, as well as structured data such as lists and records. Use this module to convert domain-specific data into JSON representations for logging, configuration, or API responses.

This module implements JSON serialization and deserialization for Gendarme's internal types, converting values to and from Yojson.Safe.t. It provides functions to marshal and unmarshal typed values, encode and decode them to strings, and pack or unpack target values, enabling use cases like persisting configurations or transmitting data over APIs. The core submodule handles serialization of basic types and structured data such as lists and records. Together, they allow converting domain-specific values into JSON for logging, configuration storage, or API responses.
